* Describe data
d

* Summarize data
sum

* Drop observations with missing values
drop if incwage >= 99999998

* Merge with PCE data
sort year
merge m:1 year using ../bea/pce.dta

* Deflate wages
gen adj_wages = incwage/pce*100
gen cohort = year - age

* Keep only ages 25-30
keep if age >= 25 & age <= 30


* Check cohorts
tab cohort year

* Check average wage by cohort
egen avg_wages = wtmean(adj_wages), weight(asecwt) by(cohort)

* Plot over time
twoway line avg_wages cohort, sort ///
xlabel(#10) xtitle("Cohort Birth Year") ylabel(#5) ///
ytitle("Average Wages (2017 $)", size(medsmall)) ///
title("Average Wages (2017 $) by Cohort", ///
size(medsmall))
* Note decline after 1980 due to individuals being too young (under 40)

* Export data
save ../wage_distrib.dta, replace

* Return to main directory
cd ../..
